A vintage-style illustration of an ornate antique wooden filing cabinet with brass handles, its drawers partially open revealing colorful index cards organized in neat rows. Above the cabinet, translucent gears and clockwork mechanisms float in a warm sepia-toned atmosphere, suggesting systematic organization. Scattered around the cabinet are small ceramic jars with handwritten labels on their sides, each containing glowing orbs of different colors representing stored values. The scene has the aesthetic of a 1920s technical manual illustration with cross-hatching details, aged paper texture, and muted earth tones accented by touches of amber and copper. Soft dust motes catch light streaming from an unseen window, giving the scene a nostalgic, archival quality.
